comments.body:
Update, so here's a run on a tag: https://cirrus-ci.com/build/5093673821011968

I see in the F35 build task, it is showing a `$CIRRUS_CHANGE_IN_REPO` which matches the tagged commit but `$DEST_BRANCH` is set wrong :confused: 

@edsantiago it's critical that we only do high-reliability checks on new tags, since there's no opportunity to fix the code (w/o force-pushing).  Would you mind adding a check early on to see if `$CIRRUS_TAG` is non-empty.  If so, probably the best thing is to not check any other conditions (i.e. git merge base will probably fail), to avoid problems that can't be fixed.  Does that make sense?
